casebody.data:
Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Boughton.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Boughton (1991), 59 Ohio St. 3d 102.]

(No. 90-1706 Submitted October 17, 1990 Decided April 24, 1991.) *103J. Warren Bettis, disciplinary counsel, and Harald F. Craig III, for relator. Stanley Morganstem, for respondent. Per Curiam.

We find that respondent committed the misconduct found by the board and concur with its recommendation. Respondent is hereby publicly reprimanded. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
